VL  - 6
IS  - 1
SP  - 141
EP  - 146
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/01/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(80)90024-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393280900240
AB  - In the light of Rasche's methodological criticism of Laidler's Phillips-curve estimation for six countries we re-estimated these employing an alternative method of estimation. The empirical results prove that Rasche's reservations are justified. The estimations for three of the six countries differ considerably from those reported by Laidler.
